TextChange: Are people more likely to be happy if they focus on their personal goals or on the happiness along the way.

Some believe that happiness come by pursuing their dreams and their own  personal goals. Other believe that people are happy only when they have their minds fixed on some goal other than their own happiness. Accordingly, Hppiness comes when people focus on the happiness of others or on the improvement of humanity. Aiming at something other than their own happiness, they find happiness along the way.\n
